# Styling Guidelines

## Primary Styling Framework
Use **DaisyUI classes** as the primary styling approach. Only use raw Tailwind CSS when DaisyUI doesn't provide the needed functionality.

## Custom Theme
The project uses a custom DaisyUI theme called "grobles" with:
- Green-tinted color palette
- Light color scheme
- Custom radius and sizing variables
- Poppins font family

## Global Styles
[global.css](mdc:src/styles/global.css) contains:
- Tailwind CSS and DaisyUI imports
- Custom theme definition
- Poppins font import
- Custom animations: `fade-in` and `slide-up`

## Available Custom Animations
- `.animate-fade-in` - Fade in with scale effect (0.8s)
- `.animate-slide-up` - Slide up effect (0.6s)

## Color Scheme
The "grobles" theme uses:
- Base colors: Light greens (oklch format)
- Primary: Green accent color
- Consistent content colors for accessibility
- Custom radius and border settings

## Best Practices
- Prefer DaisyUI semantic classes over utility classes
- Use the custom theme colors consistently
- Leverage the custom animations for enhanced UX
- Maintain the established green color palette